PlatinumFreeInterval: This is negative if the patient had received treatment after the date of progression/recurrence or if the date of last platinum treatment is after the date of last follow-up.
PlatinumStatus: It describes whether the patient was resistant to platinum (chemotherapy) treatment
days_to_death: it indicates the primary treatment a success (the patient survived)
days_to_death_or_LFU: days to death or LFU (loss to follow-up). LFU refers to patients who at one point in time were actively participating in a clinical research trial, but have become lost (either by error in a computer tracking system or by being unreachable) at the point of follow-up in the trial.
daystotumorprogorrecur: days to tumor progression or recurrence
primary_therapy_outcome_success: it means the primary treatment a success (the patient survived)
